long_desc.thetext:
Your package js failed to build from source in current rawhide.
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=17728537
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_26_Mass_Rebuild
This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 26 development cycle. Changing version to '26'.
*** Bug 1424039 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
js-1.8.5-27.fc26 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 26. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-2c7a774f26

js-1.8.5-27.fc26, pam-1.3.0-2.fc26 has been pushed to the Fedora 26 testing repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report. See https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/QA:Updates_Testing for instructions on how to install test updates. You can provide feedback for this update here: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-2c7a774f26

Proposed as a Freeze Exception for 26-alpha by Fedora user pbrobinson using the blocker tracking app because:
Crasher of core functionality that uses js-1.8.5-27.fc26 and a fix to the 48 bit VA change (https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Releases/26/ChangeSet#AARCH64_-_48-bit_VA) for aarch64
Discussed in today's Blocker Review meeting. It would be great to get support for aarch64.
js-1.8.5-27.fc26, pam-1.3.0-2.fc26 has been pushed to the Fedora 26 stable repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report.

The fix for this bug broke ELinks (bug #1446545). I would suggest to rebuild all packages that were built against older versions of js-devel because the fix for this bug comes with a backward-incompatible ABI change.
